│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The transform in InstCombineSelect::foldSelectEqualityTest folds a nested     │
│ select-of-equality-tests pattern into a single equality compare of X and Y.   │
│ This is correct for plain icmp eq, but becomes incorrect in the presence of   │
│ the "samesign" flag on the icmp. The samesign modifier can cause the icmp     │
│ result to be poison when operands have different signs. In the original       │
│ pattern, the potentially-poison value is masked by select semantics (select   │
│ does not propagate poison if the non-poison arm is chosen). Replacing the     │
│ whole expression with the samesign comparison directly makes the final result │
│ poison in some cases, whereas the original was defined. Alive2 shows a        │
│ concrete counterexample.                                                      │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ - The first and only transforming point is                                    │
│ InstCombinerImpl::foldSelectEqualityTest which replaces the whole pattern     │
│ with the icmp samesign eq %X, %Y value.                                       │
│ - Alive2 error: "Target is more poisonous than source" with %X = -42, %Y = 0. │
│ Source returns false (defined), target returns poison. This means the         │
│ transform is not poison-safe.                                                 │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ - foldSelectEqualityTest matches the boolean pattern using                    │
│ m_SpecificICmp(ICMP_EQ, ...) which matches the predicate but does not account │
│ for the icmp's samesign flag.                                                 │
│ - It then returns replaceInstUsesWith(Sel, XeqY) using the existing icmp      │
│ instruction. If XeqY has hasSameSign() set, it may be poison for              │
│ differing-sign operands, even though the original expression masked that      │
│ poison via selects.                                                           │
│ - Thus, the fold is only valid if XeqY is a plain equality icmp (no           │
│ samesign), or if we can otherwise guarantee the icmp cannot be poison.        │
│ Currently, the code does not check this.                                      │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s)                                                     │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp                 │
│ - Location: Right before returning the XeqY value in foldSelectEqualityTest.  │
│ - Edit: Add a guard to bail out if the matched XeqY icmp has the samesign     │
│ flag.                                                                         │
│                                                                               │
│ Inserted code (conceptual):                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│   // Do not fold through a samesign equality, because replacing the whole     │
│   // expression with a potentially-poison compare can make the result         │
│   // more poisonous than the original (which may have masked the poison       │
│   // via selects).                                                            │
│   if (cast<ICmpInst>(XeqY)->hasSameSign())                                    │
│     return nullptr;                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ This is a conservative and correct fix. It avoids creating a more-poisonous   │
│ target. An alternative (more aggressive) fix would be to build a new plain    │
│ icmp eq X, Y (without samesign) and replace the select with it. That would be │
│ refinement-safe (less poisonous than source), but requires creating a new     │
│ instruction; the minimal change for safety is to bail out when samesign is    │
│ present.                                                                      │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ We added a safety guard in foldSelectEqualityTest to refuse the               │
│ transformation if the matched X==Y comparison carries the samesign flag. This │
│ prevents turning a value whose poison is masked by selects into a naked       │
│ poison-producing value, thereby fixing the miscompile demonstrated by Alive2. │
│ The expected effect is that the provided reproducer will no longer fold to    │
│ icmp samesign eq %X, %Y and will preserve the original semantics.             │
